HOMEMADE GRANOLA 👌🏻
•
•
Granola 😍 everyone’s favorite.. make it at home in a few easy steps! 👀 the recipe 👇🏻

Base recipe 
4C gf oats 
1/2C maple syrup 
1/2C olive or avocado oil 
Vanilla 
Cinnamon 
Sea salt 
Add in whatever toppings you like! 
(Chopped nuts, dried fruit, chocolate, nut butters) 
Mix all together. Press well on to parchment lined baking sheet. Bake on 350 for 20-25 min until golden. Let set for 30 min before breaking into cluster!!!!!!

STUFFED ARTICHOKES AND STRING BEANS 🔥
•
•
A set it and forget it one pot meal! A great addition to a holiday or weeknight dinners 👌🏻 👀 the recipes 👇🏻
———————————————————————————————
#kardioandkale
———————————————————————————————Here’s what you need 

For the artichokes 
Artichoke bottoms 
1 lb chop meat 
2-3 tbsp of rice 
2 tbsp of water 
Garlic powder 
Salt 
Allspice 
Dot of cinnamon 

String beans 
String beans 
Tons of the following spices 
Salt 
Onion powder
Cinnamon 
Garlic powder
All spice
Tumeric 
Dash of paprika 

Sauce 
1/3C water 
1/4C lemon juice 
1/4C oot
Salt 
Pepper
Garlic 
3 tbsp tomato paste 
Pinch of all spice 

Combine the meat mixture and stuff the artichokes. Sear the artichokes meat side down in some avocado oil until browned. Once browned remove from the pan and in the same pan add all the spices for the string beans and toast them in remaining oil. About 2 minutes. Add the string beans and cover and let them sauté for 10 minutes or until bright green stirring occasionally. Once they are cooked taste and adjust spices. Add the artichokes back on top bottom side down. Pour the sauce over the top. Cover let it simmer on low for 2-2.5 hours. Spoon the sauce over the artichokes mid way through and after cooking. ENJOY

COCONUT ALMOND DATE BALLS🫶🏻
•
•
#1 item to have stashed in the freezer at all times! It’s a must 👌🏻 
In a food processor combine 15-20 dates with some vanilla extract + almond extract. Pulse until combined. Add 1/2c coconut flakes and 3 tbsp of hot water. Pulse again. Transfer date mixture to a bowl. Add in 1/3-1/2C of almond flour until it forms a dough. Roll into balls. Roll dates balls in shredded coconut and freeze for 30 minutes until set! (Optional - add drizzled chocolate over the top)

MAC AND CHEESE 
•
•
Gluten free and cheesy deliciousness 🤤
Each time I make this I make it differently but sharing what I did today because it was gone in 1 minute flat🤣

Cheese sauce 
2 tbsp of butter 
1/3-1/2C of milk or heavy cream (depending on amount of pasta) 
6 slices of orange cheddar cheese 
6 slices of white cheddar cheese 
1/2C of cottage cheese blended with a splash of cream 

In a pot melt the butter and milk or cream. Add in the cheese and stir until melted. Add the blended cottage cheese to the melted cheese mixture and combine. Add a pinch of salt and dash of Tumeric. Pour over the pasta and top the pasta with panko and a drizzle of oil. Optional a drizzle of cream over the top. Bake for 30 minutes until crispy.

BURRATA WITH 🍅 SHALLOTS AND GARLIC 🥖
•
•
Isn’t it perfect?! Spring is officially in the air in NYC☀️💐
That means simple, light and delicious recipes coming your way! 
👀👇🏻
In a skillet sauté sliced shallots and minced garlic with olive oil and sea salt until fragrant. Add in whole or sliced cherry tomatoes and cover. Let the tomatoes blister and release their liquids. About 10 minutes. Press the tomatoes down add a dot of spicy honey and let it reduce for 10 more minutes. Finish off with fresh basil. Transfer to a plate and top with burrata balsamic glaze and olive oil 

Garlic crostini - gluten free toast coated in minced garlic, olive oil and garlic powder. Place in oven on 400 until crisp and golden 
ENJOY!

BLUEBERRY & CREME SMOOTHIE 🫐
•
•
All about the morning smoothies👌🏻 this is also great as a mid day snack! 
What you’ll need 
Ice ( the more the frothier the smoothie) 
Almond milk (1+1/3C) 
1 scoop of your favorite vanilla protein powder 
1/3C frozen blueberries 
2 tbsp of peanut butter 
1/4C if kefir 

Combine all of the above and blend together until creamy and smooth. Line the cup with a little kefir and pour the smoothie into the cup.. enjoy!

COTTAGE CHEESE CHEESECAKE 🍓🍰
•
•
Cottage cheese is having a moment and I’m here for it
 (even though I’ve been hiding in recipes from the beginning) make this stand alone or in your favorite crust! Top with chocolate or a berry compote you won’t even know there’s cottage cheese in it!! 

What you’ll need 
1 16oz cottage cheese + 1/2C 
1/4C heavy cream
3 eggs 
1/2C almond milk 
Vanilla 
1/3-1/2C maple syrup depending how sweet you want it 
1/4C lemon juice 

In a food processor or blender blend the cottage cheese with heavy cream until smooth. Add the eggs, lemon, almond milk, vanilla and maple syrup. Blend again until smooth and pour into a pre-baked pie crust. Bake for 1 hour. Let cool completely before serving! Best enjoyed chilled

WHOLE ROASTED CAULIFLOWER 
•
•
One of my favorite ways to enjoy cauliflower! Whole roasted on a bed of lemony yogurt with sautéed garlic, capers, dates and mint! The perfect recipe for #shavuot 
👀 the recipe 👇🏻

Steam or boil cauliflower for 8 minutes in salted water. Once boiled remove and dry well. Drizzle generously with olive oil and bake on 450 until crisp and golden. Sprinkle with sea salt and set aside. In a skillet sauté garlic in olive oil until fragrant add sliced dates and capers and sauté for 5-7 minutes. Finish off with some caper juice and chopped fresh mint. Set aside. In a bowl combine green yogurt with a little sea salt- lemon juice and lemon zest. Spread on the bottom of a plate place whole roasted cauliflower on top. Place the sautéed garlic and dare mixture on top and around the cauliflower. Finish with a drizzle of olive oil! 
Enjoy!

LEMONY BRAISED BEANS WITH SPINACH 🍋
•
•
In my bean era 🤪 These we’re so good over cauliflower steak but would be delicious with spaghetti! 👀 the recipe below👇🏻
What you’ll need 
3/4 shallots sliced 
4/5 garlic cloves sliced 
2 cans of cannellini beans 
1/3-1/4C lemon juice 
Zest of one lemon 
1-2 tbsp of honey 
2 handfuls of spinach 
Basil (optional) 

Brown shallots and garlic in a little olive oil with some salt until fragrant. Add 2 cans of cannelloni beans. Drain them but don’t rinse! Then add water to each can to get the beans on the bottom out and pour water into the bean and shallot mixture. Add 1/4C of lemon juice and zest of 1 lemon to the beans. Stir until mixed. Bring to a simmer add 1-2 tbsp of honey and simmer on low for 35/40 minutes. Add spinach and let It wilt. Once wilted ready to serve!
** Add a little hot water or more lemon as needed (longer it simmers thicker it gets) **Pair with spaghetti and parm or over cauliflower steaks! **Cauliflower steak roasted in the oven on 450 with salt and pepper until crisp

SUMMER PASTA SALAD
•
•
The pasta salad that you’ll be wanting to eat poolside! Mayo free 🤣 Pasta tossed with fresh veggies so light and refreshing! 
In case you missed the recipe in the video! 
Boil pasta according to package. Add 1 diced zucchini to the boiling pasta to blanch for a few minutes. Strain and mix with olive oil salt pepper grated garlic lemon zest and the juice from Kalamata olives - add another diced zucchini chopped spinach chopped Kalamata olives chopped dill and cannelloni beans! Toss to combine. Top with grated parm and chopped pistachios🤩

• PEA PESTO•

My favorite dish to make in the summer time! So bright and flavorful 👀 the recipe 👇🏻

What you’ll need 
1-2 bags of frozen petite peas 
1 container of mascarpone cheese 
Splash of heavy cream 
Splash of lemon juice 
Salt 
Pepper 
1-2 cloves of garlic 
A few basil leaves 
Pasta water 

Boil pasta according the package reserve some pasta water. (I used gluten free fettuccini) run the peas under boiling water for a minute or two. Drain and dry and add to a blender with mascarpone, garlic, salt, pepper, heavy cream, lemon juice basil and pasta water. Mix until smooth and silky. Pour over pasta top with chopped pistachios more peas and parmesan! Enjoy 🤩

STUFFED 🍑
•
•
Stone fruit season is the best season🫶🏻 One of my favorite summer desserts are these granola stuffed peaches with a dollop of coconut whip creme😍

How to 👀⬇️
Add your halved peaches or nectarines to a sprayed pyrex 
Crumb topping
2/3 tbsp of the following 
- almond flour 
- oats 
- gluten free flour 
- arrowroot 
- coconut flour 
- coconut sugar or brown sugar 
- slivered almonds 
Mix all together until combine and add firm coconut oil or half stick of butter and mix until batter resembles clumpy wet sand. Fill each nectarine with the crumb topping. Top with lemon zest 
Cover and bake for 30 minutes 
Uncover and add 1/4C of fresh orange juices, 3 tbsp of hot water and vanilla extract. Pour around the peaches and bake for the remaining 30 minutes uncovered.

QUINOA VEGGIE BURGERS🍔
•
•

A super quick and easy meal prep that will leave you with the most delicious lunch all week! Enjoy them in a wrap, salad or even in a sandwich! 
A few 📝
• any sautéed veggies will work as long as they are chopped small and most of the water is cooked out 
• I used frozen spinach, cauliflower rice, chopped onions, shredded carrots and chickpeas
• you can use red or tri color quiona 

Cook one full bag of quinoa according to package (17oz bag) 
Let the quinoa cook slightly add in sautéed veggies + any additions mix until we’ll combined. Adjust seasonings and add two eggs as a binder. Spray a parchment lined baking sheet. Take 1/4C measuring cup and pack in the quinoa mixture drop it on the to sprayed baking sheet and repeat. Once the tray is full spray the tops and bake on 400 for 35/40 minutes until golden and crisp (optional flip halfway through) 
Enjoy!

PRETZEL TART
•
•
Been a while since I’ve shared something 🎂🍩🍭🧁🍦🍫 on the grid… 
(Hi it’s me in the reflection) this chocolates pretzel tart is a go to dessert when hosting! 5 ingredients and can be made a day in advance.. Holiday dessert ✅

What you’ll need 
1 bag of pretzels (gf work also) 
1/2C organic cane sugar 
1c avocado oil or melted butter or non dairy substitute

2C very good quality chocolate chips 
1C of almond milk- oat or coconut milk (or regular for dairy) 

Pulse the pretzels in a food processor until a fine crumb. Add the sugar pulse 2x  and transfer to a bowl. Slowly add the oil to the sugar and pretzel mix. Once mixture reaches  wet sand consistency press it into a pie dish. 
(You may or may not need all the oil + a little more) Press the mixture into the bottom of the tart pan and up the sides.  using two fingers even out the boarder as you rotate the tart pan. Bake on 350 for 15 minutes until golden. 

In the microwave or on the stove heat up the almond milk until piping hot. Add the chocolate chips and stir until glossy and melted. (Can also just melt both together then stir) 
Pour into the pretzel crust and let it set for two hours before slicing. Top with whip cream and shaved chocolate! 
Enjoy! Tag me if you make this 🤤

🇮🇱COUS COUS N VEGGIES🇮🇱

•
•
The most comforting dish ever.. IYKYK warm cous cous with brothy veggies and chickpeas! Mmm 
 
So easy and simple to make! Fun fact @galitexpress came to my house and taught me how to make this when I had my “Hasalon” themed dinner party for my friends 🫶🏻

Drizzle a little olive oil in a pot and add your veggies (chunky pieces so they don’t disintegrate) 
Cauliflower 
Onions 
Zuchinni 
Butternut squash 
Carrots 
Add water just to cover, season well with salt and Tumeric (for color) add a bay lead and bring to a simmer until veggies are fork tender. (25/30 min) add chickpeas and continue to simmer for 20 more minutes on low! 

While the veggies are cooking. Cook your cous cous according to package. (Some just require boiling water and salt) set aside. 

Place cous cous in a bowl and spoon the veggies over the top lastly adding some of the broth. Top with parsley and enjoy! Tag me if you make this!

EGGPLANT CHICKEN 
•
•
#Shabbat cooking is hands down my favorite kind of cooking🫶🏻 This is another one of those recipes that I’ve adapted from my grandmother @eileenfonce with a few tweaks! 

What you’ll need 
2 -3 eggplants 
1 whole chicken 
1 lb chop meat 
3 tbsp of rice 

Spices 
Salt 
Pepper 
Paprika 
Garlic powder 
Onion powder 
Tiniest pinch of allspice 
1/4C water
Olive oil 

Slice 1 eggplant into rounds 
Slice the remaining eggplants vertically. Place on a well sprayed sheet tray and in the broiler for 10 minutes flipping half way through. 
While the eggplant is broiling combine the chop meat, rice, water, salt, allspice and garlic powder until combined. 

Drizzle olive oil in a roaster. Place a layer of eggplant at the bottom of the roaster. Place the chicken on top and season with salt, garlic, onion powder, paprika (both sides) place breast side down and cover with the round slices of eggplant. Take the vertically broiled eggplant and a quarter size of the meat mixture and roll It up, place seam side down around the chicken. Roll and repeat.. you can make extra meat balls with the remaining meat mixture (no water is needed but can add some if you’d like) 
Cover and bake on 350 for an hour and half! Enjoy!

CHICKEN SOUP 🥣 
•
•
Aka Jewish “penicillin” but seriously the cure to anything🫶🏻
Cozy and comforting perfect for when your under the weather or a cold night 

Chop 3 carrots 2 small potatoes 3 celery stalks and place in a 10qt pot add a little olive oil cover with water. Cut one onion in half and place in the pot with water. Bring the vegetables to a boil and add 1 tbsp of kosher salt. (Can add more if you’d like) drop two chicken breasts (bone in skinless) in the pot and bring to a simmer for 30 minutes. Once chicken is cooked remove on to a cutting board and let cool 10 min before shredding. Once chicken is shredded add back to pot and add whatever other additions you’d like (noodles or matzo balls) in this photo I added gluten free stelline that I boiled in a separate pot with some chicken stock! 

Sometimes I swap potatoes for cubed butternut squash and add a splash of lemon and dill 🤌🏻
Enjoy!

RED WINE SHORT RIBS🍷🥩
•
•
The perfect cozy weeknight meal or a great way to change up your Shabbat menu! 

What you’ll need 
Short ribs 
Vegetable or chicken broth 
Red wine 
1/4C coconut sugar 
3 tbsp of pepper corns 
Handful of garlic cloves 
2 stalks of celery chopped 
2 carrots chopped 
1 onion chopped 
1 bay leaf 
Sea salt 
Gluten free flour or regular flour

Season the short ribs with sea salt. Coat the short ribs on each side with flour. Pan sear the short ribs in avocado oil until golden brown on each side. Remove the short ribs from the pot. Add the carrots, celery, onion, garlic cloves and bay leaf to the pot. Sauté for 5 minutes. Deglaze the pan with 2/3C of red wine (1 bottle) 1/3C vegetable or chicken stock. Add the pepper corns and coconut sugar to the pot. Stir well. Add the short ribs back to the pot. Add bundle of herbs (optional) thyme and rosemary cover and cook for 3 hours. Once cooked remove the herbs and strain the liquid. Transfer the liquid to a pot bring to a simmer to thicken! ENJOY

SHEET PAN MACRO BOWL🤤
•
•
Loving sheet pan meals these days! This deconstructed macro bowl was good! 
Cook grain of choice on the side
(pictured here is couscous) 

On a tray combine any vegetables + tempeh + tofu 
I used - tomatoes, edamame, sweet potatoes, scallions and carrots. 
Spice the vegetables and proteins with herbamere, garlic powder and a pinch of nutritional yeast. Add a few dashes of sesame oil, coconut aminos, yuzu ponzu and mirin. Finish with spicy honey and bake in 400 until crispy and golden. Spoon the remaining sauce over the grains before serving
